WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.600
Hi everyone! After a long time we're starting to make

2
00:00:03.600 --> 00:00:06.680
not only short videos, but full-length ones too — brew yourself a cup of

3
00:00:06.680 --> 00:00:08.960
tea and let's go.

4
00:00:08.960 --> 00:00:12.280
New Year is coming up, and in this video I want to discuss how

5
00:00:12.280 --> 00:00:15.920
the year 2000 almost didn't happen, what happened to the franchise

6
00:00:15.920 --> 00:00:19.800
Home Alone, and what is known about the fate of the troll Kuzia.

7
00:00:19.800 --> 00:00:22.160
Let's start from the beginning.

8
00:00:22.160 --> 00:00:27.040
Imagine it's 1999. The TV is saying that

9
00:00:27.040 --> 00:00:28.640
this year has been a tough one.

10
00:00:28.640 --> 00:00:32.160
The chimes ring, and the year 1900 arrives.

11
00:00:32.160 --> 00:00:34.560
Wait, what?

12
00:00:34.560 --> 00:00:35.840
It's actually quite simple.

13
00:00:35.840 --> 00:00:38.600
Back then there were many old computers

14
00:00:38.600 --> 00:00:41.160
that could not adapt to new technologies due to

15
00:00:41.160 --> 00:00:44.760
outdated software, so for them the clock could roll over to either

16
00:00:44.760 --> 00:00:47.840
the year 1900 or year zero.

17
00:00:47.840 --> 00:00:51.000
Because of this bug, an incident occurred at a Japanese nuclear power plant

18
00:00:51.000 --> 00:00:54.840
that caused the warning system to trigger.

19
00:00:54.840 --> 00:00:57.800
However, thanks to the noise raised by various news

20
00:00:57.800 --> 00:01:03.540
outlets back in 1993, most computers in government

21
00:01:03.540 --> 00:01:08.540
institutions were replaced with new ones, so no serious consequences followed.

22
00:01:09.040 --> 00:01:11.900
If you ask someone which film they associate

23
00:01:11.900 --> 00:01:15.440
with New Year, they will most likely say Home Alone.

24
00:01:15.440 --> 00:01:18.880
But why have no new installments appeared in 3 years?

25
00:01:18.880 --> 00:01:22.280
And why is Home Alone 4 the worst one?

26
00:01:22.280 --> 00:01:24.440
Let's start from the very beginning.

27
00:01:24.440 --> 00:01:28.000
When this film project was launched, no one believed in it.

28
00:01:28.000 --> 00:01:29.840
The budget was small.

29
00:01:29.840 --> 00:01:32.840
Almost all scenes were filmed in one location.

30
00:01:32.840 --> 00:01:34.880
There were many problems during filming.

31
00:01:34.880 --> 00:01:38.400
But despite all that, the film about a little boy left

32
00:01:38.400 --> 00:01:40.520
home alone became a success.

33
00:01:40.520 --> 00:01:44.160
With a budget of 15–17 million dollars, the film grossed

34
00:01:44.160 --> 00:01:46.680
476 million dollars.

35
00:01:46.680 --> 00:01:47.680
But how?

36
00:01:47.680 --> 00:01:50.600
Precisely because the film was different from others,

37
00:01:50.600 --> 00:01:52.200
it became so special.

38
00:01:52.200 --> 00:01:55.320
A fresh idea, brilliant acting, and the inimitable

39
00:01:55.320 --> 00:01:57.000
improvisation of Macaulay Culkin.

40
00:01:57.000 --> 00:02:00.480
Fun fact: the scene where Macaulay Culkin screams

41
00:02:00.480 --> 00:02:03.400
from the aftershave lotion was complete improvisation — the idea

42
00:02:03.400 --> 00:02:05.960
impressed the director so much that he decided to make

43
00:02:05.960 --> 00:02:10.080
a reference to the painting "The Scream" in the film's poster.

44
00:02:10.080 --> 00:02:13.080
Also, the film "Angels with Dirty Faces," which

45
00:02:13.080 --> 00:02:15.840
Kevin watches in the movie, doesn't actually exist.

46
00:02:15.840 --> 00:02:18.720
This once again proves that an enormous amount of work

47
00:02:18.720 --> 00:02:20.080
went into the film.

48
00:02:20.080 --> 00:02:22.960
Naturally, the franchise was followed by a sequel.

49
00:02:22.960 --> 00:02:25.720
Home Alone 2 offers nothing new, as

50
00:02:25.720 --> 00:02:27.800
its concept remained the same.

51
00:02:27.800 --> 00:02:30.560
Only instead of a two-story house, Kevin now has

52
00:02:30.560 --> 00:02:31.560
all of New York.

53
00:02:31.560 --> 00:02:34.360
With a budget of 20 million dollars, the film grossed

54
00:02:34.360 --> 00:02:37.120
around 359 million dollars.

55
00:02:37.120 --> 00:02:39.560
Something interesting to note is that the first part

56
00:02:39.560 --> 00:02:43.160
became so popular that when filming the second one,

57
00:02:43.160 --> 00:02:46.240
people recognized the actors and disrupted the shoot.

58
00:02:46.240 --> 00:02:50.960
Also, in the second film you can spot a scene featuring Donald Trump.

59
00:02:50.960 --> 00:02:54.160
And this is where the franchise's popularity starts to decline.

60
00:02:54.160 --> 00:02:58.160
In Home Alone 3, the creators completely replaced the McCallister family

61
00:02:58.160 --> 00:03:01.400
with new characters, since the main character had by that time already

62
00:03:01.400 --> 00:03:03.920
grown up and was no longer suitable for the film.

63
00:03:03.920 --> 00:03:07.080
In addition, instead of two bumbling thieves, the film introduced

64
00:03:07.080 --> 00:03:08.080
four spies.

65
00:03:08.080 --> 00:03:10.720
Fans didn't like this, because that's not what

66
00:03:10.720 --> 00:03:11.720
they fell in love with the film for.

67
00:03:11.720 --> 00:03:14.880
As a result it grossed far less than the other installments.

68
00:03:14.880 --> 00:03:17.560
With a budget of 32 million dollars, the box office came to

69
00:03:17.560 --> 00:03:19.680
79 million dollars.

70
00:03:19.680 --> 00:03:21.520
Even so,

71
00:03:21.520 --> 00:03:23.360
I personally love this installment.

72
00:03:23.360 --> 00:03:26.600
It was the first part of this franchise that I watched.

73
00:03:26.600 --> 00:03:29.560
However, if I want to rewatch something from the first

74
00:03:29.560 --> 00:03:32.480
three Home Alone films, naturally this part

75
00:03:32.480 --> 00:03:33.800
will take a back seat.

76
00:03:33.800 --> 00:03:38.080
But even so, it wasn't the third part that killed the franchise — it was the fourth.

77
00:03:38.080 --> 00:03:40.080
Home Alone 4 was terrible.

78
00:03:40.080 --> 00:03:42.120
Its budget was 5 million dollars.

79
00:03:42.120 --> 00:03:44.360
The transfer went straight from Windows Movie Maker.

80
00:03:44.360 --> 00:03:46.240
Snow was completely absent.

81
00:03:46.240 --> 00:03:49.440
And they even managed to remove something as basic as traps.

82
00:03:49.440 --> 00:03:50.680
No, there were some.

83
00:03:50.680 --> 00:03:52.280
But in very small numbers.

84
00:03:52.280 --> 00:03:54.920
And for defense the kid mainly used a smart home system.

85
00:03:54.920 --> 00:03:58.680
I think there's no point in talking about the remaining two parts.

86
00:03:58.680 --> 00:03:59.680
Kuzia

87
00:03:59.680 --> 00:04:02.400
Or as he is known in the West, Hugo.

88
00:04:02.400 --> 00:04:05.120
He was popular in the 90s thanks to a show called

89
00:04:05.120 --> 00:04:06.920
"Call Kuzia."

90
00:04:06.920 --> 00:04:10.160
In this show you had to call a specific number,

91
00:04:10.160 --> 00:04:13.720
and if you got through, you could play the game in front of the whole country

92
00:04:13.720 --> 00:04:16.240
and possibly even win a prize.

93
00:04:16.240 --> 00:04:19.240
But what does Kuzia have to do with a New Year video?

94
00:04:19.240 --> 00:04:20.240
Let me explain.

95
00:04:20.240 --> 00:04:23.320
In the early 2000s the show lost its popularity.

96
00:04:23.320 --> 00:04:26.760
This led to even more full-fledged games in the series appearing.

97
00:04:26.760 --> 00:04:28.920
Among them are two games:

98
00:04:28.920 --> 00:04:31.520
Kuzia's New Year and Kuzia's New Year 2.

99
00:04:31.520 --> 00:04:33.120
The first part was a masterpiece.

100
00:04:33.120 --> 00:04:35.320
The plot involves a small town

101
00:04:35.320 --> 00:04:38.720
with Father Frost and his gnomes preparing for the New Year.

102
00:04:38.720 --> 00:04:41.360
But then a witch arrives and ruins everything.

103
00:04:41.360 --> 00:04:43.960
And Kuzia now helps restore it all.

104
00:04:43.960 --> 00:04:46.720
There is an atmospheric map on which you need to find

105
00:04:46.720 --> 00:04:47.920
mission houses.

106
00:04:47.920 --> 00:04:50.160
The missions themselves are placed randomly,

107
00:04:50.160 --> 00:04:52.320
which makes finding them very challenging.

108
00:04:52.320 --> 00:04:55.720
In the main square there is Father Frost's house, where

109
00:04:55.720 --> 00:04:56.720
a fairy tale will be told to you.

110
00:04:56.720 --> 00:05:00.000
The game ends with the witch checking what

111
00:05:00.000 --> 00:05:01.000
is happening in the town.

112
00:05:01.000 --> 00:05:05.080
She looks into her crystal ball and sees that it is completely snowy

113
00:05:05.080 --> 00:05:06.080
and nobody is working.

114
00:05:06.080 --> 00:05:08.920
But if we look at what's actually happening, it turns out that

115
00:05:08.920 --> 00:05:11.520
it's just a fake picture that Kuzia created.

116
00:05:11.520 --> 00:05:13.120
But there was one funny moment:

117
00:05:13.120 --> 00:05:16.120
you could see this ending without even completing the game.

118
00:05:16.120 --> 00:05:19.480
To do that, you could simply quit the game and that was it.

119
00:05:19.480 --> 00:05:22.160
When fans finished this game, they really wanted

120
00:05:22.160 --> 00:05:23.480
a second part.

121
00:05:23.480 --> 00:05:26.120
But when it came out, they were disappointed.

122
00:05:26.120 --> 00:05:28.040
The town was completely removed from the game.

123
00:05:28.040 --> 00:05:30.120
The story changed drastically.

124
00:05:30.120 --> 00:05:32.200
Also, the mini-games are very simple.

125
00:05:32.200 --> 00:05:34.880
And the game itself feels cheap.

126
00:05:34.880 --> 00:05:36.360
But why did this happen?

127
00:05:36.360 --> 00:05:40.040
The thing is, the first part was made by IT Media.

128
00:05:40.040 --> 00:05:41.720
Published by MediaHouse.

129
00:05:41.720 --> 00:05:45.680
MediaHouse saw that the first part had become very popular

130
00:05:45.680 --> 00:05:50.040
and decided to buy the rights from IT Media in order to make a second part.

131
00:05:50.040 --> 00:05:52.280
In the end they released the second part.

132
00:05:52.280 --> 00:05:55.160
But naturally they had a much smaller budget,

133
00:05:55.160 --> 00:05:57.320
which is why the game turned out terrible

134
00:05:57.320 --> 00:05:59.080
and nobody liked it.

135
00:05:59.080 --> 00:06:00.240
That's all from me.

136
00:06:00.240 --> 00:06:02.600
Thank you very much for watching this video.

137
00:06:02.600 --> 00:06:05.720
Leave a like and subscribe to our community.

138
00:06:05.720 --> 00:06:06.720
This was Pin-KOD.

139
00:06:06.720 --> 00:06:07.720
See you soon!)
